I have a terrible spatial sense, which has always made me awful at games like Tetris, with rage-quits aplenty. I wasn't sure if this game would be any different, but I took the leap and I'm glad I did. The flipped perspective makes it feel fresh, and the ability to reconnect isolated pieces onto the main mass makes it more forgiving than Tetris without dumbing down the difficulty. This game is amazing, and I highly recommend it. Definitely worth $3.
